[{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pallets/jinja/issues/comments/52799351","html_url":"https://github.com/pallets/jinja/issues/358#issuecomment-52799351","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pallets/jinja/issues/358","id":52799351,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDUyNzk5MzUx","user":{"login":"kooky","id":1606192,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE2MDYxOTI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1606192?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/kooky","html_url":"https://github.com/kooky","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kooky/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kooky/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kooky/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kooky/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kooky/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kooky/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kooky/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kooky/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kooky/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2014-08-20T15:58:21Z","updated_at":"2014-08-20T15:58:21Z","body":"Do you really need to know the type?  Are the tests like number and string not enough?\n\nhttp://jinja.pocoo.org/docs/templates/#list-of-builtin-tests\n\nI guess you could add type as a customer filter.  But this really doesn't feel very useful.\n\n```\nimport jinja2\n\nenv=jinja2.Environment()\nenv.filters['type'] = type\n\ntemplate =env.from_string(\"\"\"begin {{ note|type }} end\"\"\")\nprint(template.render(note='hello'))\nprint(template.render(note=1))\n```\n\noutput:\n\n```\nbegin <type 'str'> end\nbegin <type 'int'> end\n```\n","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pallets/jinja/issues/comments/52799351/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confus